)

LEGS (
Fig. 23A–B
). All legs with tarsus longer than metatarsus; not granulated; femur + patella of leg IV 2.41 times as long as broad; legs III and IV with articulation between femur and patella slightly oblique; tibiae III and IV with medial tactile setae; metatarsi III and IV with basal tactile setae; arolium as long as claws, distally broadened and undivided, claws simple and not serrate.

