GENITALIA (
Fig. 24E
). 2 setae arranged linearly on sternite 2 and 8 setae linearly on sternite 3 below opening.

CEPHALOTHORAX. Carapace 1.15–1.29 times as long as broad; 
one paratype
with 27 setae arranged 4:6:4:6:7; variation in chaetotaXy of coXae of legs I–IV: 10:10:8:10 (ZMH A0003695), 10:10:6:8 (ZMH A0003696), 8:8:6:10 (ZMH A0003697), 10:10:8:10 (ZMH A0003698), 10:8:8:10 (ZMH A0003699); pedipalpal coxa with 8 (n =2) or 10 (n= 3) setae.
